item.title: TEPREL-1B
item.description: TEPREL-1B is a liquid bi-propellant rocket engine developed by PLD Space, a Spanish company working towards a slot in the micro satellite launchers. This engine will be used in MIURA-1 a suborbital vehicle that will be able to carry a 100kg payload to 153km and also serve as a testbed for several technologies. The available specs of the engine are as follows: Propellants: Liquid oxigen (LOX) & Rocket grade kerosne (RP1) Engine cycle: Pressure-fed (helium as pressurant) Thrust (sea level): 30kN Burn time: 122 seconds On top of this, we also know that the vehicle carries 1000l of LOX and 600l of RP1 [1][2]
